# Juggling Siteswap System

A tool for generating, analyzing, and visualizing juggling siteswap patterns. Deployed as a Blazor WebAssembly PWA at https://siteswaps.passing.zone.

## Architecture (Layered)

```
Webassembly (Blazor WASM host, pages, routing)
  └─ Siteswaps.Components (reusable Razor components, visualizations)
  └─ Siteswaps.Generator (Fluxor state, UI-facing generator logic)
       └─ Siteswaps.Generator.Core (backtracking algorithm, filters)
            └─ Siteswap.Details (domain model, validation, math)

Siteswaps.Mcp.Server (ASP.NET Core MCP server, AI tool integration)
  └─ Siteswaps.Generator.Core
  └─ Siteswap.Details
```

## Key Projects

| Project | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| `Siteswap.Details` | Domain model: `Siteswap` record, states, orbits, causal/state diagrams |
| `Siteswaps.Generator.Core` | Backtracking generator with composable `ISiteswapFilter` pipeline |
| `Siteswaps.Generator` | Fluxor state management, Blazor Razor library for generator UI |
| `Siteswaps.Components` | Shared visualization components (diagrams, graphs) |
| `Webassembly` | Blazor WASM app host |
| `Siteswaps.Mcp.Server` | MCP server exposing siteswap tools/resources/prompts via HTTP |

## Tech Stack

- .NET 10, C# with nullable enabled, warnings-as-errors
- Blazor WebAssembly with Radzen UI, Fluxor (Redux-style state), VisNetwork.Blazor
- Central Package Management (`Directory.Packages.props`)
- CSharpier for formatting (enforced in CI)
- NUnit + FluentAssertions + Verify for unit tests
- Playwright + Reqnroll for E2E tests
- ArchUnitNET for architecture enforcement
- arc42 documentation in `docs/arc42/`
